snippet.textDisplay: I really hate the word "clone" when it comes to these things. It's an innovation and most people saw this coming to the industry a little before they were announced. These are "True wireless earbuds". Saying something like the samsung galaxy buds are a clone of airpods is like saying beats are clones of bose's over-ear headphone design. It's a category of technology, like regular wired headphones or tablets. I don't hate airpods, in fact I really like the new design of them with the ear cushions (which I think should have been on the first model). Now this is me talking about things like samsung and sony's true wireless earbuds that have their own design and features and all that. I am NOT defending those pieces of garbage that are designed to look identical to airpods but are much cheaper in both price and quality like all those ones on wish and shit. THOSE are clones and are pieces of trash. Ok thank you for coming to my ted talk, have a wonderful day.

snippet.textDisplay: For me, AirPods were the easiest way to see who was rich and who wasn't. I remember the first Christmas after AirPods came out. Now for me, I am thankful that my parents ask me what I want for Christmas and they always say it can be up to $150. Other than that, Ill get some small little stocking stuffers and candy, or maybe a smaller little gift or 2 that i wasn't expecting in addition to my main present, but nothing crazy. But then I remember seeing some friend's Snapchat stories and seeing the brand new $150 AirPods they got as like a little side gift or even a stocking stuffer. Ridiculous.
